cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with tasks related to computer vision and natural language processing, which are typically covered by the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper specifically focuses on video action recognition and image annotation, which are core tasks in computer vision and multimedia. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories. The use of RNNs and backpropagation also suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.LG and cs.AI. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for image annotation, which further supports the inclusion of cs.CL as a likely sub-category.
